{{Quote|You are Jedi Knights. Responsibility. Peace. Discipline. You are the examples the galaxy looks to. Your successes will carry through the Republic and beyond. As will your mistakes. Your choices will matter, helping the Jedi maintain peace in a time of discord.|Mace Windu|<ref name="Red Blade">''[[Inquisitor: Rise of the Red Blade]]''</ref>}}
'''Jedi Knight''' was a rank within the [[Jedi Order]], referring to a [[Jedi]] [[Padawan]] who had completed their [[Jedi training|training]] and passed the [[Jedi Trials]] to become a full member of the Order.<ref name="Episode I" /> 

==History==
{{Quote|For over a thousand generations, the Jedi knights<!--decapitalization of "knights" is intentional, since the film's captions format it that way--> were the guardians of peace and justice in the old<!--decapitalization of "old" is intentional, since the film's captions format it that way--> Republic. Before the dark times, before the Empire.|Obi-Wan Kenobi, to Luke Skywalker|<ref name="Episode IV" />}}
[[File:JediKnightGeneral-SWQ20.png|thumb|left|300px|Jedi Knights served as generals during the Clone Wars.]]
In the history of the Order, a Jedi Knight was lower than a [[Jedi Master]] and needed to prove themselves worthy of the higher rank.<ref name="Dooku Captured">{{TCW|Dooku Captured}}</ref>

Unlike those who had that higher rank, Jedi Knights were unable to pursue their studies on their own terms. Master [[Porter Engle]] believed that any Jedi worthy of the title of knight put [[time]] into planning [[Unarmed combat|unarmed defense]] in case they lost their [[lightsaber]].<ref name="LotJ">''[[The High Republic: Light of the Jedi]]''</ref>

Jedi Knights, like the Order they served, were guardians of peace and justice in the [[Galactic Republic]],<ref name="Episode IV" /> and served in key [[Republic Military|military]] [[Jedi General|command roles]] during the [[Clone Wars]]. At the war's end, [[Supreme Chancellor]] [[Darth Sidious|Sheev Palpatine]]&mdash;secretly the [[Sith Lord]] [[Darth]] Sidious&mdash;issued [[Order 66]], declaring every Jedi an [[Treason|enemy of the state]]. As a result, the [[clone trooper]]s of the [[Grand Army of the Republic]] turned against their [[general]]s,<ref name="Episode III">{{Film|III}}</ref> [[Death|killing]] most of the Jedi.<ref name="Episode IV" /> 

At the end of the [[Galactic Civil War]], [[Luke Skywalker]] was the last known Jedi Knight.<ref name="Episode VI">{{Film|VI}}</ref>

{{Force-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
As confirmed by editor [[Tom Hoeler]], the term "Jedi Knight" should always see both words capitalized, as should "Knight" on its own if it refers to a Jedi Knight. "Knighthood" also needs to be capitalized, while "knighted" does not need to be.<ref name="Knight Grammar">{{Twitter|DarthInternous|status/1882078287591268413|[[Tom Hoeler]]|quote=Fun #StarWars editing facts. As regards a Jedi... Knight is capitalized (whether alone or with Jedi) knighted is NOT capitalized Knighthood IS capitalized (whether alone or with Jedi)|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/7AKut}}</ref> According to the reference book ''[[The Star Wars Book]]'', once a Jedi Knight had trained a [[Padawan]] of their own to Knighthood, they could then become a [[Jedi Master]].<ref name="SW Book">''[[The Star Wars Book]]''</ref> This, however, contradicts the events of the novel ''[[The High Republic: Into the Dark]]'', where a character rises to the level of Master without passing that requirement.<ref name="Into the Dark">''[[The High Republic: Into the Dark]]''</ref>

